#: src/concepts/patterns.md:3
msgid ""
"Adora is a dataflow framework based on pub/sub message passing. On top of "
"basic topics, the framework supports **service** (request/reply) and "
"**action** (goal/feedback/result) patterns using well-known metadata keys. "
"No changes to the daemon, coordinator, or YAML syntax are required -- the "
"patterns are implemented as conventions at the node API level."
msgstr ""
"Adora 是一个基于发布/订阅消息传递的数据流框架。在基本主题之上，该框架通过约定的元数据键支持 **service**（请求/应答）和 "
"**action**（目标/反馈/结果）模式。无需更改守护进程、协调器或 YAML 语法 -- 这些模式作为节点 API 层面的约定来实现。"

#: src/concepts/patterns.md:9
msgid "1. Topic (pub/sub)"
msgstr "1. 主题（发布/订阅）"

#: src/concepts/patterns.md:11
msgid ""
"The default pattern. A node publishes data on an output, and any node that "
"subscribes to that output receives it."
msgstr "默认模式。一个节点在输出上发布数据，订阅该输出的任何节点都会接收到它。"

